OL,3,CMan who found migrants in his lorry
OL,4,Cshocked to be hit with Border Force
OL,5,Cfine
OL,7,F"Our previous MP, Mark Harper, was
OL,8,Fvery close indeed to resolving this
OL,9,Funfortunate matter.
OL,11,F"A solution to this Border Force error
OL,12,Fwas almost in the bag. Mark had acted
OL,13,Fquickly to involve the then Home
OL,14,FSecretary, James Cleverly, and a happy
OL,15,Fending was imminent.
OL,17,F"But then, Rishi called the General
OL,18,FElection, Parliament was dissolved,
OL,19,Fand Mark was no longer allowed to be
OL,20,Finvolved.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G16/20
